steps.description:
You may be required to put a deposit down and then make occasional payments. This will also give you a chance to communicate with your host family and school and develop a relationship with them. Some exchange student organizations are more for information and may require only a few payments. If this is the case, make sure it is a trustworthy organization before signing up. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/85/Become-an-Exchange-Student-in-France-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Become-an-Exchange-Student-in-France-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/85/Become-an-Exchange-Student-in-France-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Become-an-Exchange-Student-in-France-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Understand that you may not have a choice as to where you stay in France. Some students may idealize Paris, Cannes or another part of the country, but exchange programs place students where they can find homes. You may be far away from the most famous cities in France. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ca/Become-an-Exchange-Student-in-France-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Become-an-Exchange-Student-in-France-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ca/Become-an-Exchange-Student-in-France-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Become-an-Exchange-Student-in-France-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
